	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1" facs="EHRI-ET-JMP014_01.jpg"/>
			<p>Mr. <persName ref="#ehri_et_klinger_ota">Ota <hi rend="letter-spacing: +2px">Klinger</hi></persName>, <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/3067696/prague.html">Prague I.</placeName>, <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/3067696/prague.html">Betlémská</placeName> 8, made the following statement available to the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-657" type="subject">Documentation Campaign</term>.</p>

			<p><date>1945</date>.</p>
			<p>-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>
			<p>To my <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825">mother</term>, my <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825">fiancée</term>, my comrades, and to all of those who exercised in JPT
				(Union of Proletarian Sports) with the hero of these lines, <persName
					ref="http://www.holocaust.cz/databaze-obeti/obet/93562-hanus-herrmann/" type="victim">Honza Hermann</persName>.</p>

			<p>I would like to describe for you the final moments of your true hero in life and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">death</term>.</p>

			<p>This roughly 31-year-old athlete in body and spirit, whose politically active <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826">brother</term> was killed by the occupiers, was originally a builder,
				but spent long months in the <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_ghettos-449" type="ghetto">Theresienstadt
					Ghetto</placeName> working as a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-102" type="subject"
					>cook</term> and, later, due to his skillfulness, as the leader of a <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">work</term> group. Beloved by all of his <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-483" type="subject">fellow prisoners</term> for his honesty, skill as a
				worker, and, last but not least, for his great sense of fairness, he is departing on a <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-267" type="subject">transport</term> to <placeName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-2" type="camp">Auschwitz</placeName> now. Once there, he is <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-411" type="subject">selected</term> from the thousands of the strongest to
				leave <placeName type="camp" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-2">Auschwitz</placeName>, leaving his mother to
				an uncertain fate along with the rest of the 11,000 <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-483" type="subject"
					>prisoners</term>, 10,500 of whom will be <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-698"
					type="subject">executed in the gas chambers</term>.</p>

			<p>In the <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-851" type="camp">Schwarzheide</placeName><term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-508" type="subject">labor camp</term> near <placeName type="camp"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-847">Oranienburg</placeName>, firmly believing in the victory of the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1029" type="subject">allies</term>, he <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">works</term> for 12 hours a day, except for the hours
				spent in attendance at <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-487" type="subject">roll calls</term> and on the
				way to <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">work</term>. His strong athlete’s body holds
				out against unbearable suffering, back-breaking <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556"
					>work</term>, and <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-569">hunger</term>, and he outlives
				many of his friends who are <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745">dying</term> from <term
					type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-569">starvation</term> and torture. He rejoices over, and
				suffers as a result of, the countless <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1105" type="subject"
					>airstrikes</term> that we experience in the synthetic gasoline <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-929">factory</term>. Although we have built many multi-storeyed shelters
				with 3 meter reinforced concrete ceilings, we have to wait out the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1083"
					type="subject">bombings</term> close to the <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-929"
					>factory</term> inside wooden buildings that are subjected to frequent hits.</p>

			<p>The <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1083" type="subject">bombs</term> that strike here injure comrade
					<persName ref="http://www.holocaust.cz/databaze-obeti/obet/93562-hanus-herrmann/" type="victim">Honza</persName> so slightly that
				he recovers in several months and is once more sent off to become part of a <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">work</term> group whose sole purpose is to completely
				exhaust the workers. He solemnly swears revenge upon those who ignored his injuries and sent him to be destroyed. More <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1105" type="subject">air strikes</term> land and we are the victims of the
					<term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1159">Germans</term>’ brutality. During the last
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1105" type="subject">airstrike</term>, comrade <persName
					ref="http://www.holocaust.cz/databaze-obeti/obet/93562-hanus-herrmann/" type="victim">Honza</persName> leaves the room in which we
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">eat</term> and goes to the room where we sleep.
				He wants to escape the thought that he could be hit again. The <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1083"
					type="subject">bomb</term> falls several meters from our wooden building, and many shards bounce off the concrete slabs of the
				washroom that has been reduced to dust and strike dozens of <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-483"
					type="subject">prisoners</term> who are lying on the floor of the house. Our <persName
					ref="http://www.holocaust.cz/databaze-obeti/obet/93562-hanus-herrmann/" type="victim">Honza</persName> is among the unfortunate
				ones. Shrapnel has sliced his leg open close to the groin. Everyone is heavily wounded. A punctured stomach, a ripped up back, a
				sliced off hand, and much worse. We rush to <persName ref="http://www.holocaust.cz/databaze-obeti/obet/93562-hanus-herrmann/"
					type="victim">Honza</persName>’s side. We want to wrap him in a blanket and carry him off to the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-491" type="subject">sickroom</term>. <persName
					ref="http://www.holocaust.cz/databaze-obeti/obet/93562-hanus-herrmann/" type="victim">Honza</persName> refuses, and tells us to
				take those with lighter injuries who can still be helped. He points our attention to his significant blood loss, hopeless condition,
				his maimed body. This shows what a great man he truly was. His selflessness is a quality one would be hard-pressed to find here above
				this <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">tomb</term> of thousands and millions of
				people. It made us shiver to hear his words of eternal, incomprehensibly great friendship. I don’t think I exaggerate when I state
				that such brotherhood is described only in the Bible. Our friend <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745"
					type="subject">passed away</term> 3 days later and left us with an everlasting memory – a symbol of humanity, as well as vigilance
				to make sure that those who caused these atrocities do not go unpunished. Although he helped build the medical shelters that were 5
				minutes away from our <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-508" type="subject">camp</term>, leaving a little
				bit of himself there every day, our <persName ref="http://www.holocaust.cz/databaze-obeti/obet/93562-hanus-herrmann/" type="victim"
					>Honza</persName> is taken to a wholly unfit wooden hut. Here, a <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-286">medical attendant</term>, a German <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-286" type="subject">surgeon</term>, operates on him. <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-483" type="subject">Prisoners</term> are only allowed to assist and stitch
				up heavy wounds using a plain needle used to sew bags. The <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-286">medical attendant</term> operates with a regular wood saw from the
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-508" type="subject">camp</term>’s joinery workshop, and dozens of
				our friends, victims of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1083" type="subject">bombing</term>, <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">die</term> after going through indescribable agony
				alongside tens of thousands of others worked and tortured to death.</p>

			<p>May they rest in peace.</p>

